{"rawJson":null,"m_plot":"Everyone wants to meet Arlen Faber (Jeff Daniels), the world famous author of the best-selling spiritual book Me and God, but crotchety, disgruntled Arlen simply wants to be left alone, and so far he's been successful at keeping his identity a secret. But all that changes when troubled bookstore owner Kris Lucas (Lou Taylor Pucci) discovers his home address and barters books for Arlen's words of wisdom, and a back injury leads the reclusive writer to date chiropractor and overprotective single mother Elizabeth (Lauren Graham). As Arlen's relationships with his newfound friends grow, he must come to terms with his past and the realization that he doesn't hold all the answers.","m_cast":"Jeff Daniels as Arlen Faber[2] | Lauren Graham as Elizabeth[2] | Lou Taylor Pucci as Kris Lucas[2] | Thomas Roy as Riley Lucas[4] | Olivia Thirlby as Anne[2] | Kat Dennings as Dahlia[2] | Nora Dunn as Terry Fraser | Max Antisell as Alex | Tony Hale as Mailman[2] | Annie Corley as Mrs. Gold | Peter Patrikios as Ross | Richard Barlow as Paul | Richard Lyntton as Journalist","m_reception":"The Answer Man received negative reviews. Rotten Tomatoes gives it a score of 33% based on reviews from 40 critics.[5]","m_production":null,"m_sequel":null,"m_based_on":null,"m_directed_by":"John Hindman","m_produced_by":"Kevin Messic Jana Edelbaum","m_screenplay_by":null,"m_story_by":null,"m_starring":"Jeff Daniels | Lauren Graham | Lou Taylor Pucci | Olivia Thirlby | Kat Dennings | Thomas Roy","m_music_by":"Teddy Castellucci","m_cinematography":"Oliver Bokelberg","m_edited_by":"Gerald B. Greenberg","m_production_company":null,"m_distributed_by":"Magnolia Pictures","m_release_dates":"July 24, 2009 (2009-07-24) |  |  |  | ","m_running_time":"95 minutes","m_country":"United States","m_language":"English","m_budget":null,"m_box_office":"$47,865[1] | The Answer Man (previously titled The Dream of the Romans and Arlen Faber) is a 2009 romantic comedy film written and directed by J